games.comment: Andy Dalton started well, going 10-of-15 for 81 yards and a score. However, he slowed down in the second quarter and injured his hand right after halftime. He's listed as probable for next week's game at Denver.

Andy Dalton had an efficient performance on Sunday afternoon. Despite the fact that the Bengals only had the ball for 25 minutes, Dalton was able to orchestrate some solid downfield drives that allowed the Bengals to build an early lead. Granted, he was gifted field position inside the Denver 5-yard line in the first quarter, but he did convert that into a touchdown. Dalton's downfield accuracy in this contest was very good.
